s to focus the map camera on a specified Geometry with the minimum zoom level. For example, focus user attention on a route line."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Follow Puck viewport automatically tracks the user’s position on the map.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Idle viewport is activated when the user interacts with the map. You can also set it to interrupt the ongoing viewport transition animation.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Typically, you set viewport via two methods: by setting the constant initial viewport, or passing the viewport ","type":"text"},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The former method is handy to set viewport only once, at map initialization time:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct StaticViewport: View {","    var body: some View {","        \/\/ Focus camera on Disneyland at zoom 10.","        Map(initialViewport: .camera(center: disneyland, zoom: 10))","    }","}","","private let disneyland = CLLocationCoordinate(latitude: 33.812092, longitude: -117.918976)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The latter method allows you to programmatically update the viewport at any time, with or without animations:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct UserLocationMap: View {","    \/\/ Initially, focus camera on US Disneyland.","    @State var viewport: Viewport = .camera(center: disneyland, zoom: 10)","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Map(viewport: $viewport)","            Button(\"Jump to Paris Disneyland\") {","                \/\/ Later, update viewport with the different settings.","                viewport = .camera(center: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 48.868, longitude: 2.782), zoom: 12)","            }","            Button(\"Animate to User\") {",